Salesforce Flow

Flow Orchestration

Manually suspend a running orchestration. Fix the errors in an orchestration run that failed within the previous 14 days because of a recoverable error, and then resume the orchestration run. See all of your assigned orchestration work items for a record and select the one to complete first.

- Suspend and Resume an Orchestration: Manually suspend a running orchestration.
- Resume a Failed Orchestration: Fix errors in failed orchestrations within 14 days and resume.
- Select the Orchestration Work Item to Complete: See assigned work items for a record and select one to complete.
- Use Omni-Channel Routing with Work Items: Route work items based on routing logic.
- Configure Conditions More Easily with the Is Blank Operator in Orchestrations: Check text values or data types for null using the Is Blank operator.
